ctdlswTConnUp.name: ctdlswTConnUp
ctdlswTConnUp.description: This trap is sent each time a transport connection becomes enabled on this DLSw.

ctdlswTConnDown.name: ctdlswTConnDown
ctdlswTConnDown.description: This trap is sent each time a transport connection becomes disabled on this DLSw.

portSegmenting.name: portSegmenting
portSegmenting.description: When a port goes from operational to segmented, a trap will be generated. For these purposes, the port state will be sampled every XXX seconds, thus it will be statistically possible to miss oscillating circuits.

portUnsegementing.name: portUnsegementing
portUnsegementing.description: When it is detected that a previously segmented port has gone operational, a trap will be generated. This is also sampled, thus a trap may not be generated for each transition.

portLinkUp.name: portLinkUp
portLinkUp.description: This trap will be generated when it is determined that a MAU has been attached to the MMAC. This is only appropriate for MIMs that support the concept of a link state.

portLinkDown.name: portLinkDown
portLinkDown.description: This trap will be generated when a previously attached MAU is removed or powered down. Again, this is only appropriate for MIM's that support link state.

srcaddrNew.name: srcaddrNew
srcaddrNew.description: This trap will be generated when the MMAC detects the existence of a new source address on one of it's ports.

srcaddrTimeout.name: srcaddrTimeout
srcaddrTimeout.description: This trap will indicate that the MMAC has not detected a packet generated by this source address within a certain timeout.

boardRemoval.name: boardRemoval
boardRemoval.description: This trap will be generated when the MMAC detects that a MIM has been removed.

boardInsertion.name: boardInsertion
boardInsertion.description: This trap will generated when the MMAC determines that a new board has been inserted.

redundActivePortInCircuitFailed.name: redundActivePortInCircuitFailed
redundActivePortInCircuitFailed.description: This trap will be generated when the active port in a redundant circuit has failed polling. This will indicate the activation of redundancy.

redundPortActivated.name: redundPortActivated
redundPortActivated.description: This trap indicates that a new port has been activated in a redundant circuit. This does NOT indicate that this port is usable, but is being tested. If the port fails, a failure trap (above) will be generated.

redundPortTestFailed.name: redundPortTestFailed
redundPortTestFailed.description: This trap will be generated when the MMAC executes it's periodic redundancy diagnostics and finds one of the ports in a redundant circuit has failed. This message will not indicate that redundancy has been activated, just that the port has failed and should be fixed before it is needed.

boardTrafficThresholdExceeded.name: boardTrafficThresholdExceeded
boardTrafficThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when the traffic (good packets per time interval) has been exceeded for a particular MIM.

boardErrorThresholdExceeded.name: boardErrorThresholdExceeded
boardErrorThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when packets of the selected error type exceeds a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for a particular MIM.

boardCollsionThresholdExceeded.name: boardCollsionThresholdExceeded
boardCollsionThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when collisions exceed a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for a particular MIM.

portTrafficThresholdExceeded.name: portTrafficThresholdExceeded
portTrafficThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when the traffic (good packets per time interval) has been exceeded for a particular port.

portErrorThresholdExceeded.name: portErrorThresholdExceeded
portErrorThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when packets of the selected error type exceeds a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for a particular port.

portCollsionThresholdExceeded.name: portCollsionThresholdExceeded
portCollsionThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when collisions exceed a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for a particular port.

portTypeChanged.name: portTypeChanged
portTypeChanged.description: This trap indicates that a port has changed from a station port to a trunk port or vice versa.

portSecurityViolation.name: portSecurityViolation
portSecurityViolation.description: This trap is generated when a source address other than those locked to a port is seen.

portViolationReset.name: portViolationReset
portViolationReset.description: This trap is generated when management intervention has reset a port after a violation has occurred.

envTempWarm.name: envTempWarm
envTempWarm.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the temperature within a MIM has reached a WARM condition.

envTempHot.name: envTempHot
envTempHot.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the temperature within a MIM has reached a HOT condition.

envVoltageLow.name: envVoltageLow
envVoltageLow.description: This trap is generated when a power supply's voltage is LOW.

envTempNormal.name: envTempNormal
envTempNormal.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the temperature within a MIM has returned to a NORMAL state.

envVoltageNormal.name: envVoltageNormal
envVoltageNormal.description: This trap is generated when all power supplies' voltage have returned to a NORMAL state.

fanFail.name: fanFail
fanFail.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the system fans have failed.

fanNormal.name: fanNormal
fanNormal.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the system fans have returned to normal.

boardBroadcastThresholdExceeded.name: boardBroadcastThresholdExceeded
boardBroadcastThresholdExceeded.description: This trap is generated when the broadcast packets (per time interval) have exceeded the threshold for the given board.

portBroadcastThresholdExceeded.name: portBroadcastThresholdExceeded
portBroadcastThresholdExceeded.description: This trap is generated when the broadcast packets (per time interval) have exceeded the threshold for the given port.

systemVoltageLow.name: systemVoltageLow
systemVoltageLow.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the power to the EMME is low.

systemVoltageNormal.name: systemVoltageNormal
systemVoltageNormal.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the power to the EMME has returned to normal.

epimRemoval.name: epimRemoval
epimRemoval.description: This trap is generated when it is detected that an EPIM has been removed.

epimInsertion.name: epimInsertion
epimInsertion.description: This trap is generated when it is detected that an EPIM has been inserted.

rptrTrafficThresholdExceeded.name: rptrTrafficThresholdExceeded
rptrTrafficThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when the traffic (good packets per time interval) has been exceeded for a network.

fanMisconfigured.name: fanMisconfigured
fanMisconfigured.description: This trap is generated when the device detects that the system fans are misconfigured.

rptrErrorThresholdExceeded.name: rptrErrorThresholdExceeded
rptrErrorThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when packets of the selected error type exceeds a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for an entire network.

rptrCollsionThresholdExceeded.name: rptrCollsionThresholdExceeded
rptrCollsionThresholdExceeded.description: This trap will be generated when collisions exceed a threshold percentage of the good packets for a particular interval for an entire network.

rptrLockStatusChanged.name: rptrLockStatusChanged
rptrLockStatusChanged.description: This trap is generated when the status of the address lock changes for a certain network.

rptrBroadcastThresholdExceeded.name: rptrBroadcastThresholdExceeded
rptrBroadcastThresholdExceeded.description: This trap is generated when the broadcast packets (per time interval) have exceeded the threshold for the given repeater.

srcAddressPortLockStatusChange.name: srcAddressPortLockStatusChange
srcAddressPortLockStatusChange.description: This trap is generated when a change to the source address locking is detected at the port level.

chBoardInsertion.name: chBoardInsertion
chBoardInsertion.description: This trap will generated when the MMAC determines that a new board has been inserted.

portSecureStateChanged.name: portSecureStateChanged
portSecureStateChanged.description: This trap is generated when the status of the secure state changes for a specific port.

rptrLearnStateChanged.name: rptrLearnStateChanged
rptrLearnStateChanged.description: This trap is generated when network learning is reset. When learning is reset, all secure addresses on each port, within the network, will be deleted and ports will learn source addresses, again.

rptrPortGrpLearnStateChanged.name: rptrPortGrpLearnStateChanged
rptrPortGrpLearnStateChanged.description: This trap is generated when port group learning is reset. When learning is reset, all secure addresses on each port, within the port group, will be deleted and ports will learn source addresses, again.

rptrPortLearnStateChanged.name: rptrPortLearnStateChanged
rptrPortLearnStateChanged.description: This trap is generated when learning on a port is reset. When learning is reset, all secure addresses on the port will be deleted and the port will learn source addresses, again.

rptrLearnModeChanged.name: rptrLearnModeChanged
rptrLearnModeChanged.description: This trap is generated when network learn mode is changed between one-time learn mode and continuous learn mode.

portGrpLearnModeChanged.name: portGrpLearnModeChanged
portGrpLearnModeChanged.description: This trap is generated when the port group learn mode is changed between one-time learn mode and continuous learn mode.

portLearnModeChanged.name: portLearnModeChanged
portLearnModeChanged.description: This trap is generated when the port learn mode is changed between one-time learn mode and continuous learn mode.

fpportActivated.name: fpportActivated
fpportActivated.description: This trap is generated when a port is activated in redundancy due to another port failing.

interfacePortInsertion.name: interfacePortInsertion
interfacePortInsertion.description: This trap will be generated when it is detected that an interface port has been inserted.

interfacePortRemoval.name: interfacePortRemoval
interfacePortRemoval.description: This trap will be generated when it is detected that an interface port has been removed.

interfacePortLinkUp.name: interfacePortLinkUp
interfacePortLinkUp.description: This trap will be generated when it is determined that a port on a strictly bridging interface (not a 'repeater') has been connected to a LAN. This is only appropriate for ports that support the concept of a link state.

interfacePortLinkDown.name: interfacePortLinkDown
interfacePortLinkDown.description: This trap will be generated when a previously attached bridging port has been disconnected from a LAN. This is only appropriate for ports that support the concept of a link state.

portInserted.name: portInserted
portInserted.description: This trap is sent when a stations port's link state turns on while the management state of the port is Enabled.

portDeInserted.name: portDeInserted
portDeInserted.description: This trap is sent when a stations port's link state turns off while the management state of the port is Enabled.

ringSpeedFault.name: ringSpeedFault
ringSpeedFault.description: This trap is sent when a board enters the ring speed fault state due to a station or ring port attaching to the board as a different speed than the board is configured for.

ringSpeedFaultCleared.name: ringSpeedFaultCleared
ringSpeedFaultCleared.description: This trap is sent when a board leaves the ring speed fault state.

ringPortFaulted.name: ringPortFaulted
ringPortFaulted.description: This trap is sent when a ring port wraps when its management state is Active, without regard for the selected type of the ring port.

ringPortFaultCleared.name: ringPortFaultCleared
ringPortFaultCleared.description: This trap is sent when a ring port unwraps when its management state is Active, without regard for the selected type of the ring port.

beaconState.name: beaconState
beaconState.description: This trap occurs when a Beacon is detected on the ring while the ring is in the Operational state, or when the Beacon contains different information than the last Beacon received.

beaconStateCleared.name: beaconStateCleared
beaconStateCleared.description: This trap occurs when a ring returns to the Operational state.

stationAdded.name: stationAdded
stationAdded.description: This trap is sent when a new station address is added to the security allowed list

stationRemoved.name: stationRemoved
stationRemoved.description: This trap is sent when a station is rejected from the ring with a REMOVE MAC command sent by the ring security.

ringConfigurationChanged.name: ringConfigurationChanged
ringConfigurationChanged.description: This trap is sent when the TRMM has built a new station map.

faultRecoveryPortRemoved.name: faultRecoveryPortRemoved
faultRecoveryPortRemoved.description: This trap is sent after a fault recovery condition has been corrected, and reports that a port was removed in the process of correcting the condition.

faultRecoveryBoardBypassed.name: faultRecoveryBoardBypassed
faultRecoveryBoardBypassed.description: This trap is sent after a fault recovery condition has been corrected, and reports that a board was bypassed in the process of correcting the condition.

portViolation.name: portViolation
portViolation.description: This trap is sent when a port link state turns on and the port's management state is Disabled.

portViolationCleared.name: portViolationCleared
portViolationCleared.description: This trap is sent when a port link state turns off and the port's management state is Disabled.

faultRecoveryOscillation.name: faultRecoveryOscillation
faultRecoveryOscillation.description: This trap is sent when the ring has oscillated several times within a short amount of time. The ring is considered oscillating if it has failed a short time after recovering.

ringPurgeThreshold.name: ringPurgeThreshold
ringPurgeThreshold.description: This trap is sent when ring purge errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

amErrorsThreshold.name: amErrorsThreshold
amErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when Active Monitor errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

tokenErrorsThreshold.name: tokenErrorsThreshold
tokenErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when Token errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

claimTokenThreshold.name: claimTokenThreshold
claimTokenThreshold.description: This trap is sent when claim tokens have exceeded the specified threshold value.

lostFramesThreshold.name: lostFramesThreshold
lostFramesThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost Frame count has exceeded the specified threshold value.

beaconStateThreshold.name: beaconStateThreshold
beaconStateThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Beacon State count has exceeded the specified threshold value.

frameCountThreshold.name: frameCountThreshold
frameCountThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the frame count has exceeded the specified threshold value.

lineErrorsThreshold.name: lineErrorsThreshold
lineErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the line errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

internalErrorsThreshold.name: internalErrorsThreshold
internalErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost internal errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

burstErrorsThreshold.name: burstErrorsThreshold
burstErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost burst errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

acErrorsThreshold.name: acErrorsThreshold
acErrorsThreshold.description: This trap is sent when address/copied errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

receiverCongestionThreshold.name: receiverCongestionThreshold
receiverCongestionThreshold.description: This trap is sent when receiver congestion errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

removeStationFailure.name: removeStationFailure
removeStationFailure.description: This trap is sent when a station breaks through security and cannot be removed from the ring.

ringSpeedPortFault.name: ringSpeedPortFault
ringSpeedPortFault.description: This trap is generated when a port enters the ring speed fault state due to a station or ring port attaching to the port at a different speed than the port is configured for.

ringSpeedPortFaultCleared.name: ringSpeedPortFaultCleared
ringSpeedPortFaultCleared.description: This trap is generated when a port leaves the ring speed fault state.

stnPortInserted.name: stnPortInserted
stnPortInserted.description: This trap is sent when a stations port's link state turns on while the management state of the port is Enabled.

stnPortDeInserted.name: stnPortDeInserted
stnPortDeInserted.description: This trap is sent when a stations port's link state turns off while the management state of the port is Enabled.

boardRingSpeedFault.name: boardRingSpeedFault
boardRingSpeedFault.description: This trap is sent when a 'active NON-93 series' board enters the ring speed fault state due to a station or ring port attaching to the board as a different speed than the board is configured for.

boardRingSpeedFaultCleared.name: boardRingSpeedFaultCleared
boardRingSpeedFaultCleared.description: This trap is sent when a board leaves the ring speed fault state.

ringPortWrapped.name: ringPortWrapped
ringPortWrapped.description: This trap is sent when a ring port wraps when its management state is Active, without regard for the selected type of the ring port.

ringPortWrapCleared.name: ringPortWrapCleared
ringPortWrapCleared.description: This trap is sent when a ring port unwraps when its management state is Active, without regard for the selected type of the ring port.

beaconingState.name: beaconingState
beaconingState.description: This trap occurs, if beacon recovery is enabled, when Beaconing, Ring Purging or Claim Tokens are detected on the ring while the ring is in the Operational state, or when the Beacon contains different information than the last Beacon received.

beaconingStateCleared.name: beaconingStateCleared
beaconingStateCleared.description: This trap occurs when a ring returns to the Operational state.

stnAdded.name: stnAdded
stnAdded.description: This trap is sent when a new station is added to the security allowed list.

stnRemoved.name: stnRemoved
stnRemoved.description: This trap is sent when a station is rejected from the ring with a REMOVE MAC command sent by the ring security.

removeStnFailure.name: removeStnFailure
removeStnFailure.description: This trap is sent when a station breaks through security and cannot be removed from the ring.

ringSecurityPortRemoved.name: ringSecurityPortRemoved
ringSecurityPortRemoved.description: This trap is sent when a ring security break has been corrected, and reports that a port was removed (disabled) in the process of correcting the condition.

beaconRecoveryPortRemoved.name: beaconRecoveryPortRemoved
beaconRecoveryPortRemoved.description: This trap is sent after a fault recovery condition has been corrected, and reports that a port was removed in the process of correcting the condition.

beaconRecoveryPortGroupBypassed.name: beaconRecoveryPortGroupBypassed
beaconRecoveryPortGroupBypassed.description: This trap is sent after a fault recovery condition has been corrected, and reports that a port group was bypassed in the process of correcting the condition.

beaconRecoveryBoardBypassed.name: beaconRecoveryBoardBypassed
beaconRecoveryBoardBypassed.description: This trap is sent after a fault recovery condition has been corrected, and reports that a board was bypassed in the process of correcting the condition.

portLinkViolation.name: portLinkViolation
portLinkViolation.description: This trap is sent when a port link state turns on and the port's management state is Disabled.

portLinkViolationCleared.name: portLinkViolationCleared
portLinkViolationCleared.description: This trap is sent when a port link state turns off and the port's management state is Disabled.

ringPurgeTotalThreshold.name: ringPurgeTotalThreshold
ringPurgeTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when ring purge errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

amErrorsTotalThreshold.name: amErrorsTotalThreshold
amErrorsTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when Active Monitor errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

tokenErrorsTotalThreshold.name: tokenErrorsTotalThreshold
tokenErrorsTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when Token errors have exceeded the specified threshold value.

claimTokenTotalThreshold.name: claimTokenTotalThreshold
claimTokenTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when claim tokens have exceeded the specified threshold value.

lostFramesTotalThreshold.name: lostFramesTotalThreshold
lostFramesTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost Frame count has exceeded the specified threshold value.

frameCountTotalThreshold.name: frameCountTotalThreshold
frameCountTotalThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the frame count has exceeded the specified threshold value.

lineErrorsStnThreshold.name: lineErrorsStnThreshold
lineErrorsStnThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the line errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

internalErrorsStnThreshold.name: internalErrorsStnThreshold
internalErrorsStnThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost internal errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

burstErrorsStnThreshold.name: burstErrorsStnThreshold
burstErrorsStnThreshold.description: This trap is sent when the Lost burst errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

acErrorsStnThreshold.name: acErrorsStnThreshold
acErrorsStnThreshold.description: This trap is sent when address/copied errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

receiverCongestionStnThreshold.name: receiverCongestionStnThreshold
receiverCongestionStnThreshold.description: This trap is sent when receiver congestion errors have exceeded the specified threshold value for the station.

ringSpeedPortFaulted.name: ringSpeedPortFaulted
ringSpeedPortFaulted.description: This trap is generated when a port enters the ring speed fault state due to a station or ring port attaching to the port at a different speed than the port is configured for.

ringSpeedPortFaultedCleared.name: ringSpeedPortFaultedCleared
ringSpeedPortFaultedCleared.description: This trap is generated when a port leaves the ring speed fault state.

tpimInserted.name: tpimInserted
tpimInserted.description: This trap is generated when a TPIM is installed.

tpimRemoved.name: tpimRemoved
tpimRemoved.description: This trap is generated when a TPIM is removed.

neighborNotificationInc.name: neighborNotificationInc
neighborNotificationInc.description: This trap is sent each time the neighbor notification (ring poll) does not complete.

fltRecoveryOscillation.name: fltRecoveryOscillation
fltRecoveryOscillation.description: This trap is sent when the ring has oscillated (in and out of beaconing) when beacon recovery is enabled. The ring is considered oscillating if it has failed 21 secs after recovering from the previous.

ringPollFailureEventCorrected.name: ringPollFailureEventCorrected
ringPollFailureEventCorrected.description: This trap is sent after the management module successfully recovered the Ring Poll Failure condition.

ringPollFailureEventNotCorrected.name: ringPollFailureEventNotCorrected
ringPollFailureEventNotCorrected.description: This trap is sent after the management module has failed to recover the Ring Poll Failure condition. The interesting information includes the interface number and the MAC address of the last successful ring poll station.

sPVP.name: sPVP
sPVP.description: This trap indicates that a SPVP was rerouted. The variables indicates the address of a rerouted spvp, the time stamp of when rerouting occurred, and the cause of rerouting. The cause codes are as follows: Unallocated (unassigned) number = 1 No route to specified transit network = 2 No route to destination = 3 Normal call clearing = 16 User busy = 17 No user responding = 18 Call rejected = 21 Number changed = 22 User rejects all calls with calling line identification restriction (CLIR) = 23 Destination out of order = 27 Invalid number format (address incomplete) = 28 Response to STATUS ENQUIRY = 30 Normal, unspecified = 31 Requested VPCI/VCI not available = 35 VPCI/VCI assignment failure = 36 User cell rate not available = 37 Network out of order = 38 Temporary failure = 41 Access information discarded = 43 No VPCI/VCI available = 45 Resource unavailable, unspecified = 47 Quality of Service unavailable = 49 Bearer capability not authorized = 57 Bearer capability not presently available = 58 Service or option not available, unspecified = 63 Bearer capability not implemented = 65 Unsupported combination of traffic parameters = 73 AAL parameters cannot be supported = 78 Invalid call reference value = 81 Identified channel does not exist = 82 Incompatible destination = 88 Invalid endpoint reference = 89 Invalid transit network selection = 91 Too many pending add party requests = 92 Mandatory information element missing = 96 Message type non-existent or not implemented = 97 Information element non existent or not implemented = 99 Invalid information element contents = 100 Message not compatible with call state = 101 Recovery on timer expiry = 102 Incorrect message length = 104 Protocol error, unspecified = 111

sPVC.name: sPVC
sPVC.description: This trap indicates that a SPVC was rerouted. The variables indicates the address of a rerouted spvc, the time stamp of when rerouting occurred, and the cause of rerouting. The cause codes are as follows: Unallocated (unassigned) number = 1 No route to specified transit network = 2 No route to destination = 3 Normal call clearing = 16 User busy = 17 No user responding = 18 Call rejected = 21 Number changed = 22 User rejects all calls with calling line identification restriction (CLIR) = 23 Destination out of order = 27 Invalid number format (address incomplete) = 28 Response to STATUS ENQUIRY = 30 Normal, unspecified = 31 Requested VPCI/VCI not available = 35 VPCI/VCI assignment failure = 36 User cell rate not available = 37 Network out of order = 38 Temporary failure = 41 Access information discarded = 43 No VPCI/VCI available = 45 Resource unavailable, unspecified = 47 Quality of Service unavailable = 49 Bearer capability not authorized = 57 Bearer capability not presently available = 58 Service or option not available, unspecified = 63 Bearer capability not implemented = 65 Unsupported combination of traffic parameters = 73 AAL parameters cannot be supported = 78 Invalid call reference value = 81 Identified channel does not exist = 82 Incompatible destination = 88 Invalid endpoint reference = 89 Invalid transit network selection = 91 Too many pending add party requests = 92 Mandatory information element missing = 96 Message type non-existent or not implemented = 97 Information element non existent or not implemented = 99 Invalid information element contents = 100 Message not compatible with call state = 101 Recovery on timer expiry = 102 Incorrect message length = 104 Protocol error, unspecified = 111

deviceDiagnosticMessage.name: deviceDiagnosticMessage
deviceDiagnosticMessage.description: This trap is generated for diagnostic purposes.

bridgeStatusChanged.name: bridgeStatusChanged
bridgeStatusChanged.description: This trap is generated when the status of the bridge changes.

aquiredDatabaseFull.name: aquiredDatabaseFull
aquiredDatabaseFull.description: This trap is generated when the acquired portion of the bridge's filtering database is full.

boardPortActivate.name: boardPortActivate
boardPortActivate.description: This Trap is generated when Front Panel Redundancy changes the active port.

boardNightVision.name: boardNightVision
boardNightVision.description: This trap is generated when night vision turns off or on. If power to the device is lost, this trap is sent with a value of 0, indicating that power has been lost but the device is running on 'night vision'. If power is not restored within 10 minutes, the device shuts down completely. If power is restored in that time frame, the trap is sent with a value of 1 indicating as such.

snmpLostContact.name: snmpLostContact
snmpLostContact.description: A LostContact signifies that a the Cabletron hub has lost contact with the destination IP address host/device. This trap is only sent at the 'trap-wait' intervals. Note that this trap indicates a poll failure, not a threshold failure. Threshold alarms are generated independently. The snmpPollDestination indicates the lost device.

snmpThresholdTrap.name: snmpThresholdTrap
snmpThresholdTrap.description: This trap signifies that an OID value/threshold comparison has failed. The snmpOIDObject specifies which Object Identifier and instance (destination IP address, owner IP address, and sequence number) was used to trigger the alarm condition. The snmpOIDDestination indicates the node address that failed the OID poll.

snmpReestabContact.name: snmpReestabContact
snmpReestabContact.description: A ReestabContact signifies that a the Cabletron hub has reestablished contact with the destination IP address host/device. This trap is sent immediately after contact has been reestablished.

ctBroadcastThresholdReached.name: ctBroadcastThresholdReached
ctBroadcastThresholdReached.description: This trap is generated when the configured broadcast threshold on a port is reached and will include the slot number and port number the threshold was reached on.

ctLecStatus.name: ctLecStatus
ctLecStatus.description: This trap is generated when the operational state of the LAN Emulation Client has changed.

fddiPortConnectStateChange.name: fddiPortConnectStateChange
fddiPortConnectStateChange.description: This trap is generated for FDDI port connection state changes. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiSMTMasterPortIncrease.name: fddiSMTMasterPortIncrease
fddiSMTMasterPortIncrease.description: This trap is generated whenever there is an increase in the number of SMT master ports.

fddiSMTMasterPortDecrease.name: fddiSMTMasterPortDecrease
fddiSMTMasterPortDecrease.description: This trap is generated anytime there is a decrease in the number of SMT master ports.

fddiPortAction.name: fddiPortAction
fddiPortAction.description: This trap is generated for every action against a FDDI port. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiPortLerAlarm.name: fddiPortLerAlarm
fddiPortLerAlarm.description: This trap is generated when the long term link error rate, fddimibPORTLerEstimate, crosses the fddimibPORTLerAlarm threshold. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiModuleFNBbypassed.name: fddiModuleFNBbypassed
fddiModuleFNBbypassed.description: This trap is generated when a FDDI module is bypassed on the FNB.

fddiModuleFNBinserted.name: fddiModuleFNBinserted
fddiModuleFNBinserted.description: This trap is generated when a FDDI module is inserted on the FNB.

fddiMACRMTState.name: fddiMACRMTState
fddiMACRMTState.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the FDDI ring state. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiMACCurrentPath.name: fddiMACCurrentPath
fddiMACCurrentPath.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the insertion of the MAC to the FDDI ring. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiSMTCFState.name: fddiSMTCFState
fddiSMTCFState.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the attachment configuration for the station or concentrator. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiRingTopology.name: fddiRingTopology
fddiRingTopology.description: This trap is generated when there is a change in the attachment configuration for the station or concentrator. It provides information additional to fddiSMTCFState, twisted ring conditions in particular. The variables are found in the Cabletron SMT MIB.

fddiMACFrameErrorRatio.name: fddiMACFrameErrorRatio
fddiMACFrameErrorRatio.description: This trap is generated when the frame error ratio exceeds the frame error threshold, fddimibMACFrameErrorThreshold. The variables are found in IETF FDDI MIB RFC-1512.

fddiMACDuplicateMACAddress.name: fddiMACDuplicateMACAddress
fddiMACDuplicateMACAddress.description: This trap is generated when the SMT detects a duplicate MAC address on the ring.

contLogicalChangesTrap.name: contLogicalChangesTrap
contLogicalChangesTrap.description: This trap is generated when any change occurs in the contLogicalEntryTable group of the container MIB.

contPhysicalChangesTrap.name: contPhysicalChangesTrap
contPhysicalChangesTrap.description: This trap is generated when any change occurs to contPhysicalEntryTable group of the container MIB.

rtrIpEventLogChange.name: rtrIpEventLogChange
rtrIpEventLogChange.description: This trap is generated for changes to IP event log.

rtrIPXEventLogChange.name: rtrIPXEventLogChange
rtrIPXEventLogChange.description: This trap is generated whenever an entry is made to the router IPX event log for where nwIpEventSeverity has a value of highest(1).

rtrDecIVEventLogChange.name: rtrDecIVEventLogChange

chEnvAmbientTempChanges.name: chEnvAmbientTempChanges
chEnvAmbientTempChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the chassis ambient temperature crosses over a threshold value of either one of the chassis set thresholds chEnvAmbientHot, chEnvAmbientWarm, chEnvAmbientCool, or chEnvAmbientCold to another. This trap is also sent when the chassis temperature sensor is detected to be broken or not supported.

chEnvHumidityChanges.name: chEnvHumidityChanges
chEnvHumidityChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the chassis humidity crosses a threshold value of either chEnvHumidityMoist, or chEnvHumidityDry, or when the humidity sensor is detected to be broken or not supported.

boardEnvTempChanges.name: boardEnvTempChanges
boardEnvTempChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the board temperature crosses over a threshold value of either one of the board set thresholds boardEnvTempHot, boardEnvTempWarm, boardEnvTempCool, or boardEnvTempCold to another. This trap is also sent when the board temperature sensor is detected to be broken or not supported.

boardEnvTempRelChanges.name: boardEnvTempRelChanges
boardEnvTempRelChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the board temperature relative to the chassis ambient temperature crosses a threshold value of either boardEnvTempRelHot, or boardEnvTempRelWarm. This trap is also sent when either temperature sensor located on the board or on the chassis is detected to be broken or not supported.

boardEnvTempMaxFanRelChanges.name: boardEnvTempMaxFanRelChanges
boardEnvTempMaxFanRelChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the board temperature relative to the chassis ambient temperature crosses a threshold value of either boardEnvTempMaxFanRelHot, or boardEnvTempMaxFanRelWarm when all fans in the chassis are operating at there maximum speed. This trap is also sent when either temperature sensor located on the board or on the chassis is detected to be broken or not supported.

chPowerMainVoltageChanges.name: chPowerMainVoltageChanges
chPowerMainVoltageChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the chassis main voltage rail deviates and causes the chPowerMainVoltageStatus to switch state from powerOK(1), overCurrent(2), overVoltage(3), or underVoltage(4) to another.

chPowerDiagVoltageChanges.name: chPowerDiagVoltageChanges
chPowerDiagVoltageChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the chassis diag voltage deviates and causes the chPowerDiagVoltageStatus to switch state from powerOK(1), overCurrent(2), overVoltage(3), or underVoltage(4) to another.

termPowerVoltageChanges.name: termPowerVoltageChanges
termPowerVoltageChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's termination unit changes state and causes the termPowerStatus to switch from any states to either powerOK(1), overVoltage(3), or underVolatge(4) state.

boardPowerVoltageChanges.name: boardPowerVoltageChanges
boardPowerVoltageChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's power line voltage deviates and causes the boardPowerStatus to switch from any states to either powerOK(1), overVoltage(4), or underVoltage(5) state.

termPowerModule1Changes.name: termPowerModule1Changes
termPowerModule1Changes.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's front panel button changes state and causes the termPowerModule1Status to switch state from either one of normal(1), iNBaFault(2), iNBbFault(3), fault(4), termModuleNotInstalled(5) to another.

termPowerModule2Changes.name: termPowerModule2Changes
termPowerModule2Changes.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's front panel button changes state and causes the termPowerModule2Status to switch state from either one of normal(1), iNBaFault(2), iNBbFault(3), fault(4), termModuleNotInstalled(5) to another.

chEnvFanChanges.name: chEnvFanChanges
chEnvFanChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the chassis fan changes over its status from either one value unknown(1), normal(2), testing(3), slow(4), inoperative(5), or off(6) to another.

boardPowerCurrentChanges.name: boardPowerCurrentChanges
boardPowerCurrentChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's power line current deviates and causes the boardPowerStatus to switch from any states to powerOK(1), or overCurrent(3) state.

boardPowerFrontPanelChanges.name: boardPowerFrontPanelChanges
boardPowerFrontPanelChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's front panel button state changes, it is caused when the boardPowerLocalStatus switching state from either one of resetRequest(1), powerDownRequest(2), powerOnRequest(3), or normal(4) to another.

boardPowerOperationalChanges.name: boardPowerOperationalChanges
boardPowerOperationalChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's DC-DC converter power supply voltage deviates and causes the boardPowerOperationalStatus to switch state from powerOn(1), powerOff(2), reset(3), overVoltage(4), underVoltage(5), overCurrent(6), overCurrentShutdown(7), temperatureShutdown(8), remotePowerOff(9), powerConservationShutdown(10), or frontPanelPowerOff(11) to another.

psEnvTempChanges.name: psEnvTempChanges
psEnvTempChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the power supply temperature crosses over a threshold value of either one of the power supply set thresholds psEnvTempHot, psEnvTempWarm, psEnvTempCool, or psEnvTempCold to another. This trap is also sent when the power supply temperature sensor is detected to be broken or not supported.

psEnvFanChanges.name: psEnvFanChanges
psEnvFanChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the power supply fan changes over its status from either one value unknown(1), normal(2), testing(3), slow(4), inoperative(5), or off(6) to another.

psPowerVoltageChanges.name: psPowerVoltageChanges
psPowerVoltageChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's power line voltage deviates and causes the psPowerStatus to switch from any states to either powerOK(1), overVoltage(4), or underVoltage(5) state.

psPowerCurrentChanges.name: psPowerCurrentChanges
psPowerCurrentChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's power line current deviates and causes the psPowerStatus to switch from any states to powerOK(1), or overCurrent(3) state.

psPowerAdminChanges.name: psPowerAdminChanges
psPowerAdminChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the power supply power line changes state from one operational mode to another switching between powerOn(1) and powerOff(2).

psPowerOperationalChanges.name: psPowerOperationalChanges
psPowerOperationalChanges.description: This trap is generated for each and every time the module's DC-DC converter power supply voltage deviates and causes the psPowerOperationalStatus to switch state from either one of powerOn(1), powerOff(2), reset(3), overVoltage(4), underVoltage(5), overCurrent(6), overCurrentShutdown(7), temperatureShutdown(8), or remotePowerOff(9) to another.

upsLineFail.name: upsLineFail
upsLineFail.description: This trap is generated in the event of an AC utility line failure.

upsLineFailRecovery.name: upsLineFailRecovery
upsLineFailRecovery.description: This trap is generated when the UPS switches back to line, and only if the upsLineFail trap was issued first.

upsLowBattery.name: upsLowBattery
upsLowBattery.description: This trap is generated in the event that the UPS's battery is found to be low.

upsLowBatteryRecovery.name: upsLowBatteryRecovery
upsLowBatteryRecovery.description: This trap is generated when the UPS's battery has charged above the low-battery point, and only if the upsLowBattery trap was issued first.

upsAbnormalCondition.name: upsAbnormalCondition
upsAbnormalCondition.description: This trap is generated in the event that the UPS has entered an abnormal condition, such as an overload or trip on low battery. This trap is also sent when the UPS is first turned on.

upsAbnormalConditionRecovery.name: upsAbnormalConditionRecovery
upsAbnormalConditionRecovery.description: This trap is generated when the UPS has recovered from an abnormal condition, and only if the upsAbnormalCondition trap was issued first.

upsShuttingDown.name: upsShuttingDown
upsShuttingDown.description: This trap is generated in the event that the UPS has been ordered to shut itself, or the load, off over the serial line.

upsReplaceBattery.name: upsReplaceBattery
upsReplaceBattery.description: This trap is generated when the UPS's battery test has determined that a UPS battery is unable to retain adequate charge. This trap will be generated every five hours until a new battery test is run or the UPS is turned off.

upsExtMeasAlarm.name: upsExtMeasAlarm
upsExtMeasAlarm.description: This trap is generated when the External Measurement Unit has detected that an ambient temperature or humidity limit extreme has been exceeded, or that one of the contact closure inputs has changed from the selected `normal' state. In the case of multiple alarms, a trap is generated for every alarm condition detected. In addition, the trap is sent every two minutes whenever an alarm condition exists. It is discontinued when all alarm conditions are reset. This trap is sent only for alarm states that have been enabled.

nvmpUdefTrap.description: This trap is generated when a new NVMP trap is sent that does not have an SNMP counterpart.

activePortInATMRedundancyFailed.name: activePortInATMRedundancyFailed
activePortInATMRedundancyFailed.description: This trap will be generated when the active port, on a physical ATM interface that has redundancy enabled, has failed (become quiet).

aTMRedundantPortActivated.name: aTMRedundantPortActivated
aTMRedundantPortActivated.description: This trap indicates that a new port has been activated on a physical ATM interface that has redundancy enabled. This does not indicate that this port is usable, but that it is being tested as a possible replacement.

aTMRedundanctPortTestFailed.name: aTMRedundanctPortTestFailed
aTMRedundanctPortTestFailed.description: This trap will be generated when the phyRedundIfTestTOD or the phyRedundIfPerformTest has tested a port and determined that it is not usable. The port should be fixed prior to it being needed.

aTMRedundPrimaryPortSkipped.name: aTMRedundPrimaryPortSkipped
aTMRedundPrimaryPortSkipped.description: This trap will be generated when redundancy finds that the primary port as designated be PhyRedundIfPrimaryPort is usable but cannot be used because PhyRedundIfPrimaryRevert is set to manual (2). This trap is generated only when redundancy is enabled (PhyRedundIfStatus is enable (1)) and the active port fails.
